===Idiom===

'''negotiorum gestio'''

Legal: specifically Roman Dutch Law whereby: 
*a [[gestor]]
*acts on behalf of a [[principal]] 
*for the benefit of the principal, 
*without the principal's consent. 
*The action must be ratified by the principal.
==Latin==
===Etymology===
From ''negotior - atus'' to carry on business + ''gestio - onis'' to manage.
===Idiom===
see English definition above.
